{"id":25,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":25,"title":"Chapter 22: Alma’s Mission to Ammonihah","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 22"],["h1","Alma’s Mission to Ammonihah"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p3"},"Alma worried about the Nephites’ wickedness, so he decided to spend all his time preaching the gospel. He chose Nephihah to replace him as chief judge."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/4.7,18-19"},"Alma 4:7, 18–19"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p5"},"Alma taught the gospel throughout the land. When he tried to preach in Ammonihah, the people would not listen. They threw him out of the city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.1"},"Alma 5:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.8-9,11,13"},"Alma 8:8–9, 11, 13"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p7"},"Alma was sad that the people of Ammonihah were so wicked. He left to go to another city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.13-14"},"Alma 8:13–14"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p9"},"An angel appeared and comforted Alma. The angel told him to go back to Ammonihah and preach again. Alma hurried back."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.15-16,18"},"Alma 8:15–16, 18"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p11"},"Alma was hungry. As he entered the city, he asked a man for some food. An angel had told the man that Alma would come and that Alma was a prophet of God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.19-20"},"Alma 8:19–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p13"},"This man, Amulek, took Alma to his home and fed him. Alma stayed with Amulek and his family for many days. He thanked God for Amulek’s family and blessed them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.21-22,27"},"Alma 8:21–22, 27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p15"},"Alma told Amulek about his calling to teach the people of Ammonihah. Amulek went with Alma to teach the people. The Holy Ghost helped them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/8.24-25,30"},"Alma 8:24–25, 30"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p17"},"Alma told the people to repent or God would destroy them. He said Jesus Christ would come and save those who had faith in him and repented."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/9.12,26-27"},"Alma 9:12, 26–27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p19"},"The people of Ammonihah became angry. They tried to throw Alma into prison, but the Lord protected him."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/9.31-33"},"Alma 9:31–33"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p21"},"Then Amulek began to teach. Many of the people knew Amulek; he was not a stranger as Alma was. He told them about the angel he had seen."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/9.34"},"Alma 9:34"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/10.4,7"},"Alma 10:4, 7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p23"},"Amulek said Alma was a prophet of God and spoke the truth. The people were surprised to hear Amulek’s testimony."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/10.9-10,12"},"Alma 10:9–10, 12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f12"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_12.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p25"},"Some of the people became angry, especially one wicked man named Zeezrom. They tried to trick Amulek with questions, but he told them he knew about their plan."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p26"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/10.13-17,31"},"Alma 10:13–17, 31"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_13.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p27"},"Zeezrom wanted to destroy everything that was good. He would cause problems, and then people would pay him money to solve the problems he had created."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p28"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/11.20-21"},"Alma 11:20–21"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f14"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_14.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p29"},"Zeezrom could not trick Amulek, so he offered him money to say there is no God. Amulek knew God lives and said Zeezrom knew it too but loved money more than God."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p30"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/11.22,24,27"},"Alma 11:22, 24, 27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f15"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_15.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p31","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p31"},"Then Amulek taught Zeezrom about Jesus and about the Resurrection and eternal life. The people were amazed. Zeezrom began to shake with fear."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p32"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/11.40-46"},"Alma 11:40–46"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f16"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_16.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p33","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p33"},"Zeezrom knew that Alma and Amulek had the power of God because they knew his thoughts. Zeezrom asked questions and listened as Alma taught him the gospel."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p34","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p34"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/12.1,7-9"},"Alma 12:1, 7–9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f17"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_17.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p35","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p35"},"Some people believed Alma and Amulek and began to repent and study the scriptures."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p36"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.1"},"Alma 14:1"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f18"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_18.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p37"},"But most of the people wanted to kill Alma and Amulek. They tied the two men up and took them to the chief judge."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p38","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p38"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.2-4"},"Alma 14:2–4"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f19"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_19.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p39"},"Zeezrom was sorry he had been wicked and had taught the people lies. He begged the people to let Alma and Amulek go."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p40"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.6-7"},"Alma 14:6–7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f20"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_20.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p41","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p41"},"Zeezrom and the other men who believed Alma and Amulek’s teachings were thrown out of the city. The wicked people threw rocks at them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p42","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p42"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.7"},"Alma 14:7"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f21"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_21.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p43"},"Then the wicked people gathered the women and children who believed and threw them, along with their scriptures, into a fire."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.8"},"Alma 14:8"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_22.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p45","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p45"},"Alma and Amulek were forced to watch the women and children die in the fire. Amulek wanted to use the power of God to save them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p46","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p46"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.9-10"},"Alma 14:9–10"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f23"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_23.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p47","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p47"},"But Alma told Amulek that he was not to stop the killing because the dying people would soon be with God and the wicked people would be punished."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p48","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p48"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.11"},"Alma 14:11"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f24"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_24.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p49","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p49"},"The chief judge slapped Alma and Amulek several times and mocked them because they had not saved the burning women and children. Then he threw them into prison."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p50","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p50"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.14-17"},"Alma 14:14–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f25"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_25.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p51"},"Other evil men came to the prison and abused Alma and Amulek in many ways, including starving them and spitting on them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p52","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p52"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.18-22"},"Alma 14:18–22"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f26","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f26"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_26.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p53"},"The chief judge said if Alma and Amulek used the power of God to free themselves, he would believe. He slapped them again."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p54"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.24"},"Alma 14:24"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f27","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f27"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_27.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p55"},"Alma and Amulek stood up. Alma prayed and asked God to make them strong because of their faith in Christ."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p56"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.25-26"},"Alma 14:25–26"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f28","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f28"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_28.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p57"},"The power of God filled Alma and Amulek, and they broke the ropes that held them. The evil men were scared and tried to run but fell down."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p58","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p58"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/14.25-27"},"Alma 14:25–27"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f29","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.f29"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_025_29.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p59","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-22-almas-mission-to-ammonihah.p59"},